00:01:08.660 --> 00:01:10.670
But there you go.

00:01:10.670 --> 00:01:14.110
So anyway, it's a pretty
exciting day here at Google.

00:01:14.110 --> 00:01:15.600
And there's a lot of
things going on.

00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:17.980
And I want to get into some of
the new stuff that we're

00:01:17.980 --> 00:01:19.590
bringing to market.

00:01:19.590 --> 00:01:22.480
Just as a little bit of a level
set, one of the things

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:26.270
that we struggle with in
payments is getting people to

00:01:26.270 --> 00:01:30.180
change behavior and adopting
new ideas and new concepts.

00:01:30.180 --> 00:01:32.480
And one of the things that
we've noticed really

00:01:32.480 --> 00:01:36.140
interesting lately is the pace
of change in mobile is really

00:01:36.140 --> 00:01:38.100
dramatic and really quick.

00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:40.310
One of the things we'd heard
earlier is that people just

00:01:40.310 --> 00:01:42.520
wouldn't use the internet, at
all, for doing financial

00:01:42.520 --> 00:01:45.600
transactions back in
the late '90s.

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:46.510
But that's moved on.

00:01:46.510 --> 00:01:48.370
And now pretty much everybody's
using their credit

00:01:48.370 --> 00:01:52.690
card and making payments and
doing stuff online these days.

00:01:52.690 --> 00:01:54.880
But it's even moving faster in
mobile and that's what's

00:01:54.880 --> 00:01:57.340
really exciting about what we're
doing here with Wallet.

00:01:57.340 --> 00:01:58.400
So things are changing.

00:01:58.400 --> 00:02:00.370
Things are moving really,
really quickly.

00:02:00.370 --> 00:02:03.840
And what's really interesting
is how mobile's changing all

00:02:03.840 --> 00:02:07.130
the different ways we interact
and how we work together.

00:02:07.130 --> 00:02:09.509
I think, perhaps, most
personally is

00:02:09.509 --> 00:02:11.320
the bathroom usage.

00:02:11.320 --> 00:02:15.690
And at our house we made sure
we had Wi-Fi access points

00:02:15.690 --> 00:02:18.680
with good range so that we could
do work and keep going

00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:20.760
at the same time.

00:02:20.760 --> 00:02:22.730
But it's pretty interesting.

00:02:22.730 --> 00:02:25.200
As part of the Payments team,
one of the things we try and

00:02:25.200 --> 00:02:26.790
optimize for is making
sure that the

00:02:26.790 --> 00:02:28.330
phones work in stores.

00:02:28.330 --> 00:02:30.610
And that you can have a great
experience shopping and

00:02:30.610 --> 00:02:32.980
looking for things and
purchasing stuff.

00:02:32.980 --> 00:02:35.050
And what's unique about what
we're doing is we're starting

00:02:35.050 --> 00:02:37.560
to see an incredible number of
people looking for discounts,

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:40.870
and coupons, and offers, and
savings, and things like that

00:02:40.870 --> 00:02:42.500
with their phones.

00:02:42.500 --> 00:02:46.590
And so what's nice is that's
level setter, it's a stage

00:02:46.590 --> 00:02:48.850
setting for some of the work
we did and why we brought

00:02:48.850 --> 00:02:51.730
Google Wallet into the market.

00:02:51.730 --> 00:02:55.350
So Google Wallet is, as many
as you guys know, an

00:02:55.350 --> 00:02:57.150
opportunity for the consumer
to use their

00:02:57.150 --> 00:02:58.860
phone to make a payment.

00:02:58.860 --> 00:03:02.100
And we thought that the best way
to do that was to couple

00:03:02.100 --> 00:03:05.630
things with NFC, where we
actually have the ability to

00:03:05.630 --> 00:03:09.090
see and experience in real time
a connection from the

00:03:09.090 --> 00:03:11.410
phone to the terminal and
out into the cloud

00:03:11.410 --> 00:03:13.130
to make things happen.

00:03:13.130 --> 00:03:15.190
Google Wallet's been going
really, really great.

00:03:15.190 --> 00:03:17.770
We're really excited about
our progress today.

00:03:17.770 --> 00:03:22.070
And as part of this objective
our first and foremost goal

00:03:22.070 --> 00:03:25.390
was to kick-start an ecosystem
and to get things going.

00:03:25.390 --> 00:03:27.390
We were the first guys
to make it happen.

00:03:27.390 --> 00:03:30.950
And it's kind of fun to see a
bunch of our colleagues in the

00:03:30.950 --> 00:03:33.310
industry starting to catch on
to what seems like a pretty

00:03:33.310 --> 00:03:36.240
good idea of making payments and
doing fun things with your

00:03:36.240 --> 00:03:39.690
cell phone, as a way to do
commerce and things like that

00:03:39.690 --> 00:03:42.090
around the internet.

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:45.360
So thinking about why this
is so hard and what the

00:03:45.360 --> 00:03:46.650
challenges are.

00:03:46.650 --> 00:03:48.810
It's important to realize
how many players get to

00:03:48.810 --> 00:03:51.770
participate in the ecosystem and
how many different sorts

00:03:51.770 --> 00:03:56.090
of guys have a role
in what we do.

00:03:56.090 --> 00:03:59.100
And the real challenge here is,
as part of Google Wallet,

00:03:59.100 --> 00:04:02.230
we have to bring all of these
teams together to agree on

00:04:02.230 --> 00:04:05.080
standards, to agree on how
transactions should process,

00:04:05.080 --> 00:04:06.890
to make things work together.

00:04:06.890 --> 00:04:07.740
And it's nontrivial.

00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:10.580
Because everybody thinks
they own the customer.

00:04:10.580 --> 00:04:12.540
And every one thinks
the user is theirs.

00:04:12.540 --> 00:04:15.980
And at Google we fundamentally
believe you are the user and

00:04:15.980 --> 00:04:17.300
you get to choose.

00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:19.130
Which is why it's kind of
exciting to see a little bit

00:04:19.130 --> 00:04:22.840
more competition
in the market.

00:04:22.840 --> 00:04:25.710
And people are more interested
in giving different ways of

00:04:25.710 --> 00:04:26.920
paying with things.

00:04:26.920 --> 00:04:29.520
But it's nice to see that
there's opportunity for lots

00:04:29.520 --> 00:04:31.970
of different people to
participate in the ecosystem

00:04:31.970 --> 00:04:34.890
and still create great value
for the consumer.

00:04:34.890 --> 00:04:37.830
But don't underestimate how
difficult this is to get

00:04:37.830 --> 00:04:40.110
everybody from the banks to
the people that make the

00:04:40.110 --> 00:04:43.150
phones to the retailers to put
all of their different systems

00:04:43.150 --> 00:04:45.960
together and make it work.

00:04:45.960 --> 00:04:49.290
So talking a little bit about
momentum, as I think you guys

00:04:49.290 --> 00:04:50.590
heard in the keynote.

00:04:50.590 --> 00:04:52.520
One of the things we're really,
really proud of is the

00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:54.920
acceleration of NFC
in the real world.

00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:57.480
And to give you a sense of what
that looks like, when we

00:04:57.480 --> 00:04:59.535
kicked this thing off and we
started thinking about Google

00:04:59.535 --> 00:05:02.380
Wallet back in 2010, there was
a pretty small number of

00:05:02.380 --> 00:05:05.265
phones out there and a pretty
small number of terminals.

00:05:05.265 --> 00:05:07.970
I actually remember working at
Nokia when we launched one of

00:05:07.970 --> 00:05:10.790
the first NFC phones
back in 2004.

00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:12.890
And right then we thought
the world was

00:05:12.890 --> 00:05:13.750
going to take on fire.

00:05:13.750 --> 00:05:15.720
It was going to be three years
and there'd be tens of

00:05:15.720 --> 00:05:17.350
millions of phones out there.

00:05:17.350 --> 00:05:19.160
Didn't quite happen so much.

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:22.120
But what I'm really, really
excited to reemphasize is

00:05:22.120 --> 00:05:25.990
we're now launching and adapting
more than a million

00:05:25.990 --> 00:05:27.550
NFC phones a week.

00:05:27.550 --> 00:05:29.950
So the ecosystems growing really
fast and the rate of

00:05:29.950 --> 00:05:32.290
growth is even faster than
you would imagine.

00:05:32.290 --> 00:05:34.350
You can see the number of
terminals that are available

00:05:34.350 --> 00:05:37.110
on a worldwide basis is growing
really, really fast.

00:05:37.110 --> 00:05:39.370
And we're really excited about
the fact that there's going to

00:05:39.370 --> 00:05:42.280
be so many more places that you
can use your phone to make

00:05:42.280 --> 00:05:45.280
a payment and have things
just work beautifully.

00:05:45.280 --> 00:05:47.730
In the last two quarters we've
launched six new phones

00:05:47.730 --> 00:05:49.050
powered by Google Wallet.

00:05:49.050 --> 00:05:50.570
And that's really exciting.

00:05:50.570 --> 00:05:54.230
And we think we've got tons more
exciting products that

00:05:54.230 --> 00:05:57.550
are coming out towards
the end of this year.

00:05:57.550 --> 00:06:01.370
So I guess the next thing is,
How have we been going?

00:06:01.370 --> 00:06:02.940
What have we been doing?

00:06:02.940 --> 00:06:05.760
In Google Wallet there's been a
bunch of excitement, a bunch

00:06:05.760 --> 00:06:09.550
of adapting, and listening to
consumers and to you the

00:06:09.550 --> 00:06:12.640
developers, and everybody out
there with our products.

00:06:12.640 --> 00:06:16.040
We pushed out 14 revisions in
nine months, largely in

00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:18.900
response to a bunch of consumer
feedback of wanting

00:06:18.900 --> 00:06:21.440
to get better value out of their
phone and integrating

00:06:21.440 --> 00:06:22.970
offers into the service.

00:06:22.970 --> 00:06:25.190
We added a whole bunch of new
features and capabilities

00:06:25.190 --> 00:06:29.110
around transaction history and
support of different sorts of

00:06:29.110 --> 00:06:30.980
experiences in the store.

00:06:30.980 --> 00:06:33.620
We listened and we learned to
the complexity of making sure

00:06:33.620 --> 00:06:37.250
that the point-of-sale devices
actually work, in reality

00:06:37.250 --> 00:06:39.050
versus just in theory.

00:06:39.050 --> 00:06:41.640
And you just won't believe the
number of challenges from the

00:06:41.640 --> 00:06:44.760
fact that some of the devices,
while they have power on,

00:06:44.760 --> 00:06:46.490
aren't actually connected
to anything.

00:06:46.490 --> 00:06:48.350
And so we had people tapping
their phones and saying,

00:06:48.350 --> 00:06:49.570
What's going on?

00:06:49.570 --> 00:06:52.810
And literally, it was like this,
connected with power but

00:06:52.810 --> 00:06:55.270
not actually connected to
anything on the other side.

00:06:55.270 --> 00:06:57.850
So we've built a lot of smarts
into the app to react to those

00:06:57.850 --> 00:06:58.940
situations.

00:06:58.940 --> 00:07:01.150
And as a result the ability for
payments to come through

00:07:01.150 --> 00:07:03.410
our system is improving
day by day.

00:07:03.410 --> 00:07:06.320
We've also listened and
adapted to the various

00:07:06.320 --> 00:07:08.680
concerns around the security
of our product.

00:07:08.680 --> 00:07:11.090
And we still feel very, very
confident that this is the

00:07:11.090 --> 00:07:14.230
safest way to pay and the best
solution for you as an end

00:07:14.230 --> 00:07:17.850
user to make payments
in the industry.

00:07:17.850 --> 00:07:20.780
But what we wanted to do then,
just very quickly, is give you

00:07:20.780 --> 00:07:22.970
a sense of how's this going
with consumers.

00:07:22.970 --> 00:07:26.040
So we set up an event where we
gave people a chance to try

00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:26.950
Google Wallet.

00:07:26.950 --> 00:07:28.810
And this is a little bit of the
real-time feedback we've

00:07:28.810 --> 00:07:30.250
heard from them.

