00:07:59.540 --> 00:08:02.020
PETER HAZLEHURST: So the
exciting thing is, and what we

00:08:02.020 --> 00:08:04.120
keen to do here at Google is
make sure we have magical

00:08:04.120 --> 00:08:06.010
experiences with consumers.

00:08:06.010 --> 00:08:08.580
And what we were getting out of
Google Wallet is this sense

00:08:08.580 --> 00:08:09.970
that we're starting to deliver
on some of the

00:08:09.970 --> 00:08:11.650
benefits to the consumer.

00:08:11.650 --> 00:08:14.790
That we can help them save money
by discovering and using

00:08:14.790 --> 00:08:16.030
existing deals.

00:08:16.030 --> 00:08:17.900
We're giving them a way to store
all of their loyalty

00:08:17.900 --> 00:08:19.640
cards and payment cards
in the cloud.

00:08:19.640 --> 00:08:21.050
We're giving them the financial

00:08:21.050 --> 00:08:22.060
control that they want.

00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:24.400
And just this whole beautiful
experience of when you tap

00:08:24.400 --> 00:08:26.880
your phone, the payment
just works.

00:08:26.880 --> 00:08:30.430
But the challenge for us is
dealing with concerns the

00:08:30.430 --> 00:08:32.799
consumers have around security,
and also dealing

00:08:32.799 --> 00:08:35.500
with the fact that it doesn't
necessarily work everywhere.

00:08:35.500 --> 00:08:37.669
And so this is part of what
we're trying to solve with

00:08:37.669 --> 00:08:40.740
Google Wallet and some of the
new things we're doing.

00:08:40.740 --> 00:08:43.549
And one of the things we've
started to do as we've adapted

00:08:43.549 --> 00:08:46.250
to the market, is adapt
to the fact that real

00:08:46.250 --> 00:08:47.540
world is really important.

00:08:47.540 --> 00:08:49.310
But people have told us they
want to use their Wallet

00:08:49.310 --> 00:08:50.030
everywhere.

00:08:50.030 --> 00:08:52.520
So we've pushed everything
up into the cloud.

00:08:52.520 --> 00:08:55.270
Google Wallet in the cloud is
now available so that you can

00:08:55.270 --> 00:08:58.370
do purchases all throughout
Google, on Play, Chrome Store.

00:08:58.370 --> 00:09:01.720
You can buy books, you can buy
music, you can buy games.

00:09:01.720 --> 00:09:04.380
And it's also now available on
merchant sites, and in-app

00:09:04.380 --> 00:09:06.550
payments, and other sorts
of solutions.

00:09:06.550 --> 00:09:08.760
And you can see a little bit
more demo of some of the new

00:09:08.760 --> 00:09:10.430
stuff we're doing with
in-app payments

00:09:10.430 --> 00:09:12.160
later on this afternoon.

00:09:12.160 --> 00:09:14.730
Fundamentally, everything you
do with Google Wallet is

00:09:14.730 --> 00:09:17.270
stored in the cloud, made
available across all the

00:09:17.270 --> 00:09:20.100
places we make Google
available.

00:09:20.100 --> 00:09:22.330
So going forward we said to
ourselves, There must be

00:09:22.330 --> 00:09:24.820
another solution and
another concern.

00:09:24.820 --> 00:09:27.140
And the question is, How do you
store things like coupons

00:09:27.140 --> 00:09:30.105
and tickets and gift cards and
all of these other things that

00:09:30.105 --> 00:09:32.180
you keep track of in
your daily life?

00:09:32.180 --> 00:09:34.550
And that's where we started
to evolve Google.

00:09:34.550 --> 00:09:37.130
And what we wanted to start to
focus in on is, How do I keep

00:09:37.130 --> 00:09:38.690
track of all of this
information?

00:09:38.690 --> 00:09:41.500
And how do I make it easy
to save it in my wallet?

00:09:41.500 --> 00:09:43.540
And that's what we're here
to talk about right now.

00:09:43.540 --> 00:09:45.750
So we're talking about a new
feature, a new capability

00:09:45.750 --> 00:09:47.520
called Save-to-Wallet.

00:09:47.520 --> 00:09:50.290
And Save-to-Wallet is a part
of our platform, our open

00:09:50.290 --> 00:09:53.610
ecosystem, that makes it
possible for you as an end

00:09:53.610 --> 00:09:56.210
user to save different pieces of
content that you see around

00:09:56.210 --> 00:09:57.880
the net to your Wallet.

00:09:57.880 --> 00:10:00.665
And then use it in different
places wherever you go.

00:10:00.665 --> 00:10:03.550
The implementation of which
we're offering right now is

00:10:03.550 --> 00:10:05.300
two key APIs.

00:10:05.300 --> 00:10:07.840
First of all, for saving
offers to your Wallet.

00:10:07.840 --> 00:10:10.710
This is the ability to go on
any website, anywhere, and

00:10:10.710 --> 00:10:13.860
save a discount or coupon
or some sort of savings.

00:10:13.860 --> 00:10:15.140
Store it in the Wallet.

00:10:15.140 --> 00:10:18.570
And if you need to, you can show
and scan and make it easy

00:10:18.570 --> 00:10:20.600
for the cashier to
receive it or.

00:10:20.600 --> 00:10:23.790
Or If you're a merchant, and you
know you support NFC, you

00:10:23.790 --> 00:10:25.730
can actually also
save NFC-related

00:10:25.730 --> 00:10:27.280
offers to your Wallet.

00:10:27.280 --> 00:10:28.510
So this is kind of exciting.

00:10:28.510 --> 00:10:30.510
And then we're also launching
Save to Wallet for payment

00:10:30.510 --> 00:10:31.810
cards, which is even
more interesting.

00:10:31.810 --> 00:10:34.350
But we'll get to that
in a second.

00:10:34.350 --> 00:10:36.470
So let's talk about
Save-to-Wallet for offers.

00:10:36.470 --> 00:10:39.380
In the past, we've had a pretty
easy model for our own

00:10:39.380 --> 00:10:43.250
teams at Google to support
putting discounts and savings

00:10:43.250 --> 00:10:44.000
in your Wallet.

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:45.980
And that's been working
really, really well.

00:10:45.980 --> 00:10:48.770
But what we're excited about
right now is the ability for

00:10:48.770 --> 00:10:50.380
you guys to offer the
ability to save

00:10:50.380 --> 00:10:52.040
things on your websites.

00:10:52.040 --> 00:10:55.280
